  "prompt": "Knighthood: Is it possible for a non-native British citizen to be knighted?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible for non-British citizens to be honored with knighthoods through the British honors system. However, there are specific conditions and distinctions to be aware of:\n\n1. **Honorary Knighthoods:**\n   - **Eligibility:** Foreign nationals (non-Commonwealth citizens) can be awarded honorary knighthoods in recognition of their significant contributions to the United Kingdom or to international relations.\n   - **Titles:** Unlike British citizens who receive substantive knighthoods and can use the title \"Sir\" or \"Dame,\" recipients of honorary knighthoods are **not** entitled to these prefixes unless they later become British citizens.\n   - **Examples:** Notable figures such as Bill Gates (Honorary Knight Commander of the Order of the British Empire) have received honorary titles for their contributions.\n\n2. **Conditions for Using Titles:**\n   - If an honorary knight decides to become a British citizen in the future, they may be granted the substantive rank of their honorary title and thus would be able to use \"Sir\" or \"Dame.\"\n\n3. **Commonwealth Citizens:**\n   - Citizens of Commonwealth realms (countries where the British monarch is the head of state) can receive substantive knighthoods and use \"Sir\" or \"Dame\" without needing to become British citizens.\n\n4. **Meeting the Criteria:**\n   - Recipients are typically individuals who have made exceptional contributions in fields such as the arts, sciences, charity, public service, or business.\n\n5. **Honors Committees:**\n   - Applications and nominations for honors are reviewed by committees that assess the merit and impact of the individual's contributions before recommending them for an honor.\n\n**Summary:**\nWhile non-British citizens can be recognized with knighthoods, these are usually honorary and do not confer the title \"Sir\" or \"Dame\" unless the recipient acquires British citizenship. This allows the UK to honor international individuals who have made significant contributions benefiting the nation or fostering international goodwill.",
